            <title>[AMQ-3273] Slave broker acquires lock file when Master is still alive (shared file system master/slave setup)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3273</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The change introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3237&quot; title=&quot;FileLock.tryLock() doesn&amp;#39;t work well in all environments&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQ-3237&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQ-3237&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has triggered issue with LockFile.lock() on Win7 and Win2k8. See comments to the JRE issue &lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.sun.com/view_bug.do?bug_id=6628575&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bugs.sun.com/view_bug.do?bug_id=6628575&lt;/a&gt; (bottom of the page).  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggested solution is to use this construction instead:&lt;br/&gt;
fc.lock( 0, Math.max( 1, fc.size() ), false );&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows 7, Windows Server 2008 &lt;/p&gt;</environment>
